heading: 2. The 30th day of December 2020 is appointed as the day on which
text_raw:
2. The 30th day of December 2020 is appointed as the day on which 
sections 99 and 100 of the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the 
European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 (No. 23 of 2020) shall 
come into operation.

title: Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 (No.
heading: 3. The 31st day of December 2020 at 11.00 p.m. is appointed as the day on
text_raw:
3. The 31st day of December 2020 at 11.00 p.m. is appointed as the day on 
which and the time at which Part 14 (except insofar as it is already in operation) 
of the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the European Union 
(Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 (No. 23 of 2020) shall come into operation. 

GIVEN under my Official Seal, 

22 December, 2020. 

HEATHER HUMPHREYS, 

Minister for Social Protection. 

Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
“Iris Oifigiúil” of 5th January, 2021.

EXPLANATORY NOTE 

(This note is not part of the Instrument and does not purport to be a legal 
interpretation.) 

This Order provides for the commencement of Part 14 of the Withdrawal of the 
United Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act

title: Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 (No.
heading: Part 14 amends the Social Welfare Consolidation Act 2005, concerning
text_raw:
2020. 

 Part 14 amends the Social Welfare Consolidation Act 2005, concerning 
reciprocal arrangements with other States, the recovery of benefits and 
assistance, and provides for references to the United Kingdom, to ensure the 
continuation of existing arrangements.
